omGoogleProtobufUnsafeUtilTest.java`\n\nThe test exercises Kafka’s telemetry/protobuf serialization path by:\n\n- Building an OpenTelemetry `MetricsData` payload through Kafka’s `SinglePointMetric` API.\n- Serializing it with `ClientTelemetryUtils.compress(..., CompressionType.NONE)`.\n- Parsing it back through `ClientTelemetryUtils.deserializeMetricsData(...)`.\n- Asserting the parsed metric name, value, and labels.\n\nThis should reach the shaded protobuf `UnsafeUtil` initialization and parsing paths without direct reflection or test stubs. I did not modify metadata or run tests, per the workflow rules.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_003d5486e54f1529016a0f0958259c8191a356f9bb0dbc6d22\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1561, "output": 791, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41776, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779370316129, "responseId": "resp_003d5486e54f1529016a0f094cc0f0819192b22a16eabe0984"}}
